				\begin{document}$N_{j} = \frac {G_{j}- m}{M-m},$\end{document}Nj=Gj−mM−m, where Gj is the value of the gene for patient j, M is the maximum expression value for that gene across patients in the dataset, and m is the minimum value of that gene across patients in the dataset. One consequence of this normalization procedure is that the transcriptome data has been nondimensionalized enabling integration of the dimensionless trascriptome data with the dimensionless constants. In this formulation the values of the surrogate genes parameterize the dimensionless model for each patient.

