In order to characterize the stability of these equilibrium solutions, we need to solve for the eigenvalues, λ1 and λ2, of the model at each equilibrium point. The sign of the eigenvalues, positive or negative, determines the stability and the formula for each eigenvalue tells us whether the eigenvalues can ever change sign. The eigenvalues are found by solving the characteristic polynomial equation of the Jacobian matrix, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
